body:
- Faster
- Better
- Stronger
- More localized
- No new features

- Flashlight now comes with a handful of great plugins built-in, so tons of functionality is available right out of the box.
- A better view of the plugins you have installed and the commands that are available.
- Bug fixes and performance improvements, of course.

name: v0.98.2 beta
body: - Bug fixes

name: v0.98.1 beta
body:
- Support for a brand-new, much-faster web search plugin, _Quick Web Search_
- Faster and lighter
- Plugins now automatically update to the latest version when you open Flashlight

_v0.98.1 fixes a couple small bugs in v0.98.01._

name: v.96.6

name: v0.96.5
body:
- fixes for a bunch of setup issues
- improved Korean translation
- improved command parsing

- major improvements to command-parsing accuracy
- new Swedish translation (thanks Kejk!)
- a new "New" section, for the latest and greatest plugins
- update awareness: when browsing the Plugin Directory, you'll now see which of the plugins you have are out-of-date

name: v0.96.4
body:
- major improvements to command-parsing accuracy
- new Swedish translation (thanks Kejk!)
- a new "New" section, for the latest and greatest plugins
- update awareness: when browsing the Plugin Directory, you'll now see which of the plugins you have are out-of-date

name: v0.96.3
body: Plugins can now optionally have a Preferences screen.

name: v0.96.2
body:
- a couple of stability and search-ranking fixes
- view the current version of Flashlight in About

name: v0.96.1
body:
Flashlight is faster and more stable, thanks to a brand-new search-parsing algorithm.

Messages and reminders created in Flashlight will no longer be entirely lowercase.

There's also a heap of translation improvements for various languages.

Please report any issues with this built in [Github issues](https://github.com/nate-parrott/Flashlight/issues). Thanks!

name: v0.96
body:
Flashlight is faster and more stable, thanks to a brand-new search-parsing algorithm.

Messages and reminders created in Flashlight will no longer be entirely lowercase.

There's also a heap of translation improvements for various languages.

Please report any issues with this built in [Github issues](https://github.com/nate-parrott/Flashlight/issues). Thanks!

- various performance and stability improvements
- new Greek translation (thanks [dougian](https://github.com/dougian)!)
- Fix a crashing bug for a large number of users.

name: v0.95.2
body:
- New русский (Russian) localization (thanks davochka )
- Various small bug fixes and translation improvements

name: v0.95.1
body:
Various small performance improvements and bug fixes.
More complete translations.
The ability to open plugins from the web in Flashlight to install them (e.g. [this plugin page](http://flashlight.nateparrott.com/plugin/giphy))

name: v0.95
body: Various bug fixes and small new API additions.

name: v0.94
body:
- more accurate command parsing, thanks to a couple of parsing bugs squashed
- a new API for easily writing plugins to accept dates as input (see the updated _reminder me_ plugin, for example, or _timestamp_)
- updates to German localization
- a couple other minor tweaks

name: v0.93
body:
- Flashlight works way better on OS X 10.10.2
- New Korean localization
- Search plugins right inside Flashlight
- Various visual tweaks

name: v0.92 (experimental)
body:
This build provides experimental support for OS X 10.10.2 Seed 2 (14C78C). The new seed introduces significant changes to the way Spotlight operates internally, and this intends to support them as well as older versions. If you're not running OS X 10.10.2 Seed 2, and you're having problems, please report them and move back to 0.91.

This build also includes a Korean localization (thanks [readingsnail](http://github.com/readingsnail)!).

This build will not be pushed via the automatic update process.

name: v0.91
body:
- Flashlight is way faster.
- Flashlight is way more stable.
- Flashlight is way more worldly — localized in 10 languages! (not all plugins are translated into all languages)

name: v0.9
body:
- Flashlight is now translated into German, Dutch, French, Portuguese, Spanish and Chinese.
- support for localized plugins
- support for some new plugin capabilities
- various bug fixes, including better Unicode support

name: v0.8

name: v0.71

Minor changes to support some major new plugin features.
Bug fixes and perfomance improvements, as always.

name: v0.5 Alpha

name: v0.3 Alpha
body:
- usage examples for each plugin
- better performance for the Wolfram|Alpha plugin and all web-based plugins
- New Web Search plugin

Please clean your plugins directory (in `~/Library/FlashlightPlugins`) before updating to this version. (open terminal, run `rm -rf ~/Library/FlashlightPlugins`)

name: 0.21 Alpha
body: Various small API improvements.

name: 0.2 Alpha
body: This release brings natural-language processing into the core plugin model. Plugins give examples of the commands they support, Flashlight parses queries and dispatches them to the correct plugin. As a result, Flashlight works faster and makes it easier to develop smarter natural-language-based plugins.

name: v0.11 Alpha
body: Works with Yosemite GM!
